        <body>
            <div type="edition" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="grc" resp="#JP">
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1"/><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/><supplied reason="lost">Ἀρ</supplied>τέμωνο<supplied reason="lost">ς</supplied>
                    <lb n="2"/><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/><supplied reason="lost">χ</supplied>αῖρε
                </ab>
            </div>
            <div type="apparatus">
                <listApp>
                    <app><note>Text after Manganaro and photograph.</note></app>
                    <app loc="1"><note>There is a possible trace of the final sigma, and if genuine, the sigma is four-bar, not lunate (autopsy is needed)</note></app>                
                </listApp>
            </div>
            <div type="translation">
                <p><!--translation(s) - add @xml:lang for 'en' or 'it' to div--></p>
            </div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>It is likely that the idionym, in nominative/vocative, of the deceased is missing from the left side of the stone (rather than in the space above); if so, then the original stone would be perhaps twice as wide, and Manganaro's suggestion that the word χρηστὲ is missing at the start of line 2 i plausible. There is a clear vacat above line 1, whether the top of the stone is intact or not, and also after the final word of line 2. The lunate omega is notable in a text that is otherwise very square and regular in form; the date is uncertain.</p>
            </div>
